RACE.FOOTNOTES: KHOZZY VALINTINE had a good position three wide outside tracking the pacesetter, began to close the gap when nudged on at the quarter pole, bid between horses in the three path turning for home and was edging away from the field nearing the wire. WICKED MIAH was allowed to settle trail this tight bunch in the beginning, was on hold between foes at the seven sixteenth marker, slipped up the fence two furlongs to go and rallied on the rail through the stretch to best the rest in the end. CARLA'S HONOR settled behind the frontrunner on the rail at the half, continued to keep a close eye on the leader inside in the turn, angled outside at the quarter pole, threatened four wide in upper stretch and was one paced late holding for third. GORMLEY GIRL broke out at the start, travelled in midpack between foes down the backside, was scrubbed on two deep at the midway point on the turn making little advance, angled out to the five path for the drive and found some late energy between horses to get up for a minor share at the wire. WEST PAW assumed command shortly after the break leading the field down the back straight, continued comfortably setting the pace on the turn, was headed outside by the winner at the top of the lane and tired between rivals in deep stretch. LITTLE FIRE settled near the rear three deep down the backstretch, trailed the compact field with three furlongs to go, angled out widest in the six path for the stretch run and could not reach contention finishing to the line.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SPEEDY PAL pressed for the lead in the early going, was narrowly in front setting the pace through the turn, put away his early challengers at the top of the stretch, braced for the outside challenger in mid stretch and stubbornly dug in to prevail in the end. OLD BLUE CLIFF was in the tracking flight five wide outside horses at the half, began to take closer order rallying around runners at the three furlong marker, loomed the threat in upper stretch three wide and could not get by the determined frontrunning winner in the final eighth. MENTORING battled on the front end in the three path down the backside, lost a little position between rivals midpoint on the turn to be behind the pacesetters looking for a seam at the quarter pole, angled out to the four path turning for home and picked up a runner late to capture third money. JMR SPEEDY ESCAPE was part of the pace scenario four deep at four furlong pole, prompted the front three wide on the turn outside, was in range between runners in the two path at the three sixteenths marker and faded to the wire while holding on for a minor share at the line. MUSICAL STRIDE travelled in the middle of the pack four deep down the backstretch, was shuffled back early on the turn, began to offer a finish six wide at the top of the stretch, lost path turning for home, shifted inwards to the three path in mid stretch to weave his way through runners to finish well in the end. MR. RUDY trailed the field at the half, advanced on the rail through the turn, angled five wide for the drive and showed some good late energy passing tiring runners to the finish. AMAZON FORESTER was ridden for position soon after the start to sit behind the engaging leaders on the rail into the turn, waited behind the contested front three with five sixteenths to go, was in tight surroundings on the fence at the quarter pole, had to be taken up briefly losing momentum and levelled out in the drive to the line. MARTEN STORM was away slowly to begin, appeared to be eager afterwards and rushed up between foes to be behind the front foursome at the half, inside the seven sixteenths pole was steadied, waited behind rivals midway on the turn, angled five wide for the stretch run and tired. SERENADE AT SEA settled near the rear on the rail in the beginning, lost contact with the field through the turn and pass a troubled foe in upper stretch. DANCIN' DEPUTY battled for the lead in the two path down the backside, began to back away from the front pace duel midway on the turn, was in tight and steadied at the quarter marker and was not persevered with galloping to the finish. RACE.FOOTNOTES: DEVIL'S BIT was situated in the middle of the field between horses running on the turn, angled five wide entering the stretch to be in the mix, was asked for more at the furlong pole, found another gear and was edging away when crossing the wire. FIRING BULLETS was situated on the rail not that far removed from the front pack tracking, rated kindly inside throughout the turn, found a seam at the three sixteenth pole in the five path and ran on late to get up for the runner up position. LUZ DE LA LUNA was in a good tracking position outside on hold watching the top pair up front, was coaxed three wide to bid for the lead two furlongs out, fought on until deep stretch and faded late between runners losing the photo for second. GAYELETTE was situated on the rail in midpack early on, waited on the fence behind horses travelling nicely on the turn, found a clear lane six wide at the furlong marker and closed well late to be involved for the photo for place at the finish line. MOSLER'S IMAGE leapt up in the air at the start trailing early, found running in the seven path at the three sixteenth marker and showed good late energy to finish up smartly being beaten not that far for second placing in the end. GOOGLY EYES had a good tracking position behind the engaging top pair on the turn, lost her path three wide trying for a seam in upper stretch, shifted inwards for clear run on the rail at the eighth pole and offered little turn of foot to the wire. SPIDER BELLE stalked near the back on the rail down the backside, trailed the field on the turn, angled out ten wide turning for home and passed tired runners in the final eighth. ALPHA MIA set the fractions on the backstretch and throughout the turn, was swallowed up running inside in the two path at the eighth pole and emptied out in deep stretch. JAB settled in the middle of the large field three wide outside horses, was in the mix five wide in upper stretch, could not find another gear and was outrun in the final furlong. RETAIL THERAPIST was unhurried early to be near the back of the pack in the early stages, angled out six wide turning for home, shifted inwards at the eighth pole and was never involved to the finish. MITZI prompted the pace two wide outside under a snug hold down the backside, was hard ridden offering a bid three deep between runners at the quarter marker and stopped quickly in mid stretch galloping to the wire in the end.
